<h1 class="page-header">What are Cookies</h1>
<p>Cookies are small files that a website or its Service Provider transfers to your device name desktop computer of laptops hard drive via your Web browser once allowed. This enables the website's or service provider's systems to recognize your browser, capture and store certain information. For example, we use cookies to help us remember and process the items in your shopping cart. They are also used to help us understand your preferences based on previous or current website activity, which enables us to provide you with improved services.</p>

<h1 class="page-header">What are Cookies used for?</h1>
<li>Personalization and website accessibility.</li>
<li>Understand and save your preferences for future visits.</li>
<li>Keep track of advertisements.</li>
<li>Track the site traffic in order to offer a better accessibility solution to the users.</li>
<li>Trusted third-party services that track this information on our behalf.</li>
<li><strong>NB:</strong> You can choose to have your computer notify you each time when a cookie is being sent or you can choose to turn off all cookies.You do this through your browser settings.You can check the ‘Help’ menu to learn the correct way to modify your cookies. If you turn cookies off it will turn off some of the features of the site.


